<subSubSection id="88C065359B25FFA368992EEC5260C059" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C06536BE9B25FFA368992EEC565DC254" blockId="24.[189,303,1259,1285]" box="[189,303,1259,1285]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading id="9B2D81D29B25FFA368992EEC565DC254" bold="true" box="[189,303,1259,1285]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B25FFA368992EEC565DC254" bold="true" box="[189,303,1259,1285]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C06536BE9B25FFA368992F1E54B3C2B2" blockId="24.[189,1399,1305,1508]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
The disc diameter was 
<quantity id="07229B5B9B25FFA369EE2F1E5552C265" box="[458,544,1305,1332]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="mm" value="67.0">67 mm</quantity>
. Our specimen is similar to the 
<typeStatus id="1F61881C9B25FFA36BB52F1E548AC262" box="[913,1016,1305,1331]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">holotype</typeStatus>
description by 
<bibRefCitation id="A44B4B4F9B25FFA36C892F1E5205C262" author="Doderlein L." box="[1197,1399,1305,1331]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 123" refId="ref37109" refString="Doderlein L. 1911. Uber japanische und andere Euryalae. Abhandlungen der Bayerischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch-physikalische Klasse Suppl. 5 (2): 1 - 123." type="journal article" year="1911">Döderlein (1911)</bibRefCitation>
and the description in 
<bibRefCitation id="A44B4B4F9B25FFA369F62F3B55A6C206" author="Liao Y. &amp; Clark A. M." box="[466,724,1340,1367]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref38823" refString="Liao Y. &amp; Clark A. M. 1995. The Echinoderms of Southern China. Science Press, Beijing." type="book" year="1995">Liao &amp; Clark (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, but showed some morphological variations, especially on the disc (
<figureCitation id="58E12A3B9B25FFA369762F6756D8C22B" box="[338,426,1376,1402]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[189,232,1750,1776]" captionTargetBox="[241,1348,264,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-163@25.[240,1348,264,1731]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 11. Gorgonocephalus cf. dolichodactylus Döderlein, 1911 (IDSSE EEB-SW0006). A. Dorsal aspect. B. Ventral aspect. C. Oral frame. D. Genital slit. E. Ventral disc. F. Radial shield with peripheral plate. G. Dorsal arm. H. Ventral arm. I. Lateral arm. J. Ventral view of arm base. K. Ventral view of first arm branch. L. Ventral view of second arm branch. M. Dorsal view of second arm branch. N. Coiled distal arm branches. O. Pedicellarial band. P. Pedicellariae on pedicellarial band. Abbreviations: ars = arm spine; gs = genital slit; pb = pedicellarial band; rs = radial shield; t = teeth; tp = tentacle pore. Scale bars: A = 22 mm; B = 14 mm; C = 5 mm; D, F–H, J–N = 2 mm; E, I = 1 mm; O = 500 µm; P = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419555" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419555/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Therefore, we hesitate to fully associate our specimen with 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B25FFA36CB62F67521DC22B" authorityName="Doderlein" authorityYear="1911" box="[1170,1391,1376,1402]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Gorgonocephalidae" genus="Gorgonocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euryalida" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="dolichodactylus">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B25FFA36CB62F6753D7C22B" box="[1170,1189,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B25FFA36C912F67521DC22B" box="[1205,1391,1376,1402]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">dolichodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The original description and the description in 
<bibRefCitation id="A44B4B4F9B25FFA36AD22F845482C2CF" author="Liao Y. &amp; Clark A. M." box="[758,1008,1411,1438]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref38823" refString="Liao Y. &amp; Clark A. M. 1995. The Echinoderms of Southern China. Science Press, Beijing." type="book" year="1995">Liao &amp; Clark (1995)</bibRefCitation>
mention small granules on both the dorsal and ventral disc, but the present specimen is completely naked except for the radial shields (
<figureCitation id="58E12A3B9B25FFA368E22FCE5621C2B2" box="[198,339,1481,1507]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[189,232,1750,1776]" captionTargetBox="[241,1348,264,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-163@25.[240,1348,264,1731]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 11. Gorgonocephalus cf. dolichodactylus Döderlein, 1911 (IDSSE EEB-SW0006). A. Dorsal aspect. B. Ventral aspect. C. Oral frame. D. Genital slit. E. Ventral disc. F. Radial shield with peripheral plate. G. Dorsal arm. H. Ventral arm. I. Lateral arm. J. Ventral view of arm base. K. Ventral view of first arm branch. L. Ventral view of second arm branch. M. Dorsal view of second arm branch. N. Coiled distal arm branches. O. Pedicellarial band. P. Pedicellariae on pedicellarial band. Abbreviations: ars = arm spine; gs = genital slit; pb = pedicellarial band; rs = radial shield; t = teeth; tp = tentacle pore. Scale bars: A = 22 mm; B = 14 mm; C = 5 mm; D, F–H, J–N = 2 mm; E, I = 1 mm; O = 500 µm; P = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419555" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419555/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 11A–E</figureCitation>
), which are covered by scattered granules (
<figureCitation id="58E12A3B9B25FFA36B692FCE54C7C2B2" box="[845,949,1481,1507]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[189,232,1750,1776]" captionTargetBox="[241,1348,264,1731]" captionTargetId="figure-163@25.[240,1348,264,1731]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 11. Gorgonocephalus cf. dolichodactylus Döderlein, 1911 (IDSSE EEB-SW0006). A. Dorsal aspect. B. Ventral aspect. C. Oral frame. D. Genital slit. E. Ventral disc. F. Radial shield with peripheral plate. G. Dorsal arm. H. Ventral arm. I. Lateral arm. J. Ventral view of arm base. K. Ventral view of first arm branch. L. Ventral view of second arm branch. M. Dorsal view of second arm branch. N. Coiled distal arm branches. O. Pedicellarial band. P. Pedicellariae on pedicellarial band. Abbreviations: ars = arm spine; gs = genital slit; pb = pedicellarial band; rs = radial shield; t = teeth; tp = tentacle pore. Scale bars: A = 22 mm; B = 14 mm; C = 5 mm; D, F–H, J–N = 2 mm; E, I = 1 mm; O = 500 µm; P = 200 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419555" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419555/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 11F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C06536BE9B25FFA368992C1D5260C059" blockId="24.[189,1399,1562,1800]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Pedicellarial bands are formed by approximately 12 articulating tubercles at the curved distal end of the baseplate (
<figureCitation id="58E12A3B9B25FFA369412C3A56A2C106" box="[357,464,1597,1623]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[189,232,1562,1588]" captionTargetBox="[189,1394,266,1537]" captionTargetId="figure-173@26.[189,1394,265,1537]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 12. Gorgonocephalus cf. dolichodactylus Döderlein, 1911, SEM (IDSSE EEB-SW0006). A. Plan view of base plate. B. Distal view of base plate. C. Internal view of base plate. D. Pedicellaria in the pedicellarial band. E–I. Vertebrae. E. Proximal view. F. Distal view. G. Lateral view. H. Dorsal view. I. Ventral view. Abbreviations: ap = articular pad of the base; au = auricle; D = dorsal; Dist = distal; fo = foramen of the base; fs = fossa between adjacent tubercles; hd = head of the apophysis; lp = lateral pores of the blade; mo = muscle opening; pd = pedicel of the apophysis; Prox = proximal; pt = primary tooth of the blade; sh = sheath of the base plate; st = secondary tooth; su = sulcus of tubercle head; V = ventral. Scale bars: A–C, E–F = 300 µm; D = 100 µm; G–I = 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419557/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
), and these articulations have a single foramen (
<figureCitation id="58E12A3B9B25FFA36C222C3A5303C106" box="[1030,1137,1597,1623]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[189,232,1562,1588]" captionTargetBox="[189,1394,266,1537]" captionTargetId="figure-173@26.[189,1394,265,1537]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 12. Gorgonocephalus cf. dolichodactylus Döderlein, 1911, SEM (IDSSE EEB-SW0006). A. Plan view of base plate. B. Distal view of base plate. C. Internal view of base plate. D. Pedicellaria in the pedicellarial band. E–I. Vertebrae. E. Proximal view. F. Distal view. G. Lateral view. H. Dorsal view. I. Ventral view. Abbreviations: ap = articular pad of the base; au = auricle; D = dorsal; Dist = distal; fo = foramen of the base; fs = fossa between adjacent tubercles; hd = head of the apophysis; lp = lateral pores of the blade; mo = muscle opening; pd = pedicel of the apophysis; Prox = proximal; pt = primary tooth of the blade; sh = sheath of the base plate; st = secondary tooth; su = sulcus of tubercle head; V = ventral. Scale bars: A–C, E–F = 300 µm; D = 100 µm; G–I = 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419557/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
). The distal end of the baseplate internal side becomes curved with perforations on the ventral side of the baseplate (
<figureCitation id="58E12A3B9B25FFA36CFA2C675218C12B" box="[1246,1386,1632,1658]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[189,232,1562,1588]" captionTargetBox="[189,1394,266,1537]" captionTargetId="figure-173@26.[189,1394,265,1537]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 12. Gorgonocephalus cf. dolichodactylus Döderlein, 1911, SEM (IDSSE EEB-SW0006). A. Plan view of base plate. B. Distal view of base plate. C. Internal view of base plate. D. Pedicellaria in the pedicellarial band. E–I. Vertebrae. E. Proximal view. F. Distal view. G. Lateral view. H. Dorsal view. I. Ventral view. Abbreviations: ap = articular pad of the base; au = auricle; D = dorsal; Dist = distal; fo = foramen of the base; fs = fossa between adjacent tubercles; hd = head of the apophysis; lp = lateral pores of the blade; mo = muscle opening; pd = pedicel of the apophysis; Prox = proximal; pt = primary tooth of the blade; sh = sheath of the base plate; st = secondary tooth; su = sulcus of tubercle head; V = ventral. Scale bars: A–C, E–F = 300 µm; D = 100 µm; G–I = 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419557/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12B–C</figureCitation>
). The vertebrae have a streptospondylous articulation with smooth lateral furrows and no oral bridge (
<figureCitation id="58E12A3B9B25FFA368E22CA0562AC190" box="[198,344,1703,1729]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[189,232,1562,1588]" captionTargetBox="[189,1394,266,1537]" captionTargetId="figure-173@26.[189,1394,265,1537]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 12. Gorgonocephalus cf. dolichodactylus Döderlein, 1911, SEM (IDSSE EEB-SW0006). A. Plan view of base plate. B. Distal view of base plate. C. Internal view of base plate. D. Pedicellaria in the pedicellarial band. E–I. Vertebrae. E. Proximal view. F. Distal view. G. Lateral view. H. Dorsal view. I. Ventral view. Abbreviations: ap = articular pad of the base; au = auricle; D = dorsal; Dist = distal; fo = foramen of the base; fs = fossa between adjacent tubercles; hd = head of the apophysis; lp = lateral pores of the blade; mo = muscle opening; pd = pedicel of the apophysis; Prox = proximal; pt = primary tooth of the blade; sh = sheath of the base plate; st = secondary tooth; su = sulcus of tubercle head; V = ventral. Scale bars: A–C, E–F = 300 µm; D = 100 µm; G–I = 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419557/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 12D–H</figureCitation>
). The external side of the lateral arm plate has three separate tubercle-shaped articulations with a single opening and one large muscle opening at the edge. 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B25FFA36B942CCD5230C1B5" authorityName="Doderlein" authorityYear="1911" box="[944,1346,1738,1764]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Gorgonocephalidae" genus="Gorgonocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Euryalida" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="dolichodactylus">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B25FFA36B942CCD5230C1B5" box="[944,1346,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Gorgonocephalus dolichodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first recorded from the South 
<collectingCountry id="B8CD762E9B25FFA36A332CEA552FC056" box="[535,605,1773,1799]" name="China" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">China</collectingCountry>
Sea in southeastern 
<collectingRegion id="021EF85C9B25FFA36B6A2CEA54D4C056" box="[846,934,1773,1799]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Hainan</collectingRegion>
, at a depth of 
<quantity id="07229B5B9B25FFA36C6F2CEA53D7C059" box="[1099,1189,1773,1800]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
, in 1959.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
